{
  "stem": "13258.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father-- we separated from my mother and sister on-- about two weeks, two weeks, three weeks before the outbreak of the Second War.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Second War, War broke out-- the, the war broke out in the morning hours of September 1, 1939.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We lived 16 kilometers, which is about 10 miles from the border.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My-- since, since-- as I pointed out, Katowice was about 10 miles, give and take a few, from the border.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the Poles had a big mouth at the time, said, we are going to be-- in one week, we're going to be in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He said, well, it would be safer if my mother, who was not quite well-- and she just had been-- after a bout with [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My mother and my sister would be a little bit farther away from the border.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there was school vacation still in, in, in August.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he sent them into central Poland, into a town called Konskie, K-O-N-S-K-I-E.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We had some business associates who had promised they would look after mother a little bit.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so they went two weeks before the-- two or three weeks before the war started.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I stayed with my father-- back.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father's boss was in England.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my father was running the company for which he worked at the time, which was a scrap and, and, and metal dealer.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was an intern in a brick and ceramics factory.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when the war broke out, my father went to work.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I went to work at noon on September 1st.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At about 3 o'clock, we had a shell-- a German artillery shell fall on the factory, which wounded some military people who had been using our smithy to shoe their horses.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
